Portions of the placement-optimization subsystem (under src/optimizer/) are
derived from TAP-2.5D, originally developed by the Boston University
Integrated Circuits and Systems Group:

  TAP-2.5D: Thermally-Aware Chiplet Placement Methodology for 2.5D Systems
  Yenai Ma, Leila Delshadtehrani, Cansu Demirkiran, José Luis Abellán,
    and Ajay Joshi
  Boston University, 2021
  https://github.com/bu-icsg/TAP-2.5D

  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
  See LICENSE file in the root of this repository for the full text.

The TAP-2.5D-derived files have been modified by the STAMP-2.5D authors
to add structural (von Mises stress) co-optimization, ANSYS-based
finite-element evaluation, and the multi-physics adaptive cost function
described in the STAMP-2.5D ICCD 2025 paper.
